=== 3.3 The Math

Full formula for the positional encoding matrix stem:[PE \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times d}]:

[stem]
++++
\begin{aligned}
PE[t, i] &= \sin(t \cdot \omega_{i/2})                && \text{if } i \text{ is even} \\
PE[t, i] &= \cos(t \cdot \omega_{\lfloor i/2\rfloor}) && \text{if } i \text{ is odd}
\end{aligned}
++++

where stem:[\omega_k = 1 / 10000^{2k/d}].

After building `PE`, the position-encoded input is:

[stem]
++++
\tilde{X} = X + PE \quad \in \mathbb{R}^{T \times d}
++++

The model now works with stem:[\tilde{X}] instead of `X`.
